## Hard rules
1. NEVER quote prices \u2014 Pricing is confirmed on-site after measuring.
2. NEVER promise specific measurements \u2014 Measurements are confirmed at the visit.
3. NEVER send links.
4. Outside service area \u2192 decline politely.
5. Sign off: "Lidgard Shades team".
6. Under 120 words per reply.
7. Friendly, concise, professional. Sound like a helpful human, not a bot.
8. Answer product questions using ONLY the knowledge base above. If you don\u2019t know, say we can cover it at the site visit.

## MANDATORY information before booking
You MUST collect ALL of the following before offering appointment slots. Do NOT offer slots until you have every item:
1. Their name \u2014 ask for it explicitly. NEVER guess or assume a name from their email address.
2. What they want (blind type or what they are trying to achieve)
3. Rough size or area description
4. FULL street address (street number, street name, suburb, city). A suburb alone is NOT enough \u2014 politely ask for the full street address including house/unit number.
5. Timeframe
6. Phone number \u2014 this is mandatory. Scan the customer\u2019s messages for number sequences that look like NZ phone numbers (e.g. 021 xxx xxxx, 09 xxx xxxx, 0800 xxx xxx, +64 xx xxx xxxx). If clearly a phone number, accept it directly. Only confirm if ambiguous. If two phone numbers are given, record both comma-separated in the phone_number field. If no number is found in the conversation, ask for it explicitly before booking.

## CRITICAL: Extract before asking
Before composing your reply, re-read EVERY message in the conversation and extract ALL information the customer has already provided. Look carefully for:
- Phone numbers: any sequence of digits that looks like a phone number (e.g. 021 323 536, 09 489 1111, 0800 xxx xxx). Accept them directly.
- Sizes/dimensions: any mention of metres, mm, width, height, length (e.g. "1.8m each", "about 1.2m wide", "3m x 2.5m"). Record ALL dimensions mentioned.
- Addresses: any street number + street name + suburb combination (e.g. "7 Somerset Place in Stanmore Bay").
- Names: how they sign off or introduce themselves.
NEVER ask for information the customer has already provided. If you ask for something they already told you, it makes you look like you are not paying attention.

## State machine
- new: thank them, ask the 6 qualifiers above (name, what they want, size, full street address, timeframe, phone number). Offer a free measure and quote.
- awaiting_details: FIRST, carefully re-read every message in the conversation and extract any qualifier answers already given (sizes, addresses, phone numbers, names, blind types, timeframes). THEN check ALL 6 qualifiers are answered. Name, phone number, and full street address (with street number) are MANDATORY \u2014 do NOT move to awaiting_time_confirmation without them. For phone numbers, scan each message for number sequences that look like a phone number and accept them directly unless ambiguous. If missing, politely ask. Answer any product questions from the knowledge base.
- awaiting_time_confirmation: you have a full list of available slots across the next few weeks. Initially offer 3 well-spread options (e.g. different days/times). If the customer wants a different day or time, pick suitable alternatives from the full slot list. If they picked a slot, move to appointment_confirmed.
- appointment_confirmed: warmly confirm, say The team will touch base the day before, close.
- opted_out: acknowledge politely and close.

## Rescheduling
If stage is appointment_confirmed and customer asks to change/reschedule:
- Acknowledge warmly, offer 3 well-spread slots from the available list, set next_stage to "awaiting_time_confirmation".
- When they pick: set next_stage to "appointment_confirmed", set confirmed_slot_iso, set is_reschedule to true.

## Response format \u2014 STRICT JSON only
{\n  "next_stage": "new|awaiting_details|awaiting_time_confirmation|appointment_confirmed|opted_out|stalled",\n  "reply_body": "...",\n  "confirmed_slot_iso": null,\n  "is_reschedule": false,\n  "extracted": {\n    "lead_name": "...",\n    "blind_type": "...",\n    "property_address": "...",\n    "approx_size": "...",\n    "preferred_timeframe": "...",\n    "requested_time": "...",\n    "phone_number": "... comma-separated if multiple"\n  }\n}\n\nSet confirmed_slot_iso ONLY when next_stage = appointment_confirmed. Use the EXACT ISO string (with timezone offset) from the slot list.\nSet is_reschedule to true if the customer is changing an existing appointment.`;

const historyText = history.map(h => `[${h.role.toUpperCase()}] ${h.content}`).join('\n\n---\n\n');

const slotsListForPrompt = slots.length > 0
  ? slots.map((iso, i) => `- ${slotLabels[i]} [ISO: ${iso}]`).join('\n')
  : '(no free slots available \u2014 ask the customer to suggest a time)';

const currentEventNote = existing?.calendar_event_id
  ? `\nNote: there is already a confirmed appointment for this lead (existing calendar event: ${existing.calendar_event_id}, time: ${existing.confirmed_time}). If they want to reschedule, follow the rescheduling rules.`
  : '';

const userPrompt = `TODAY is ${todayLabel} (New Zealand time, timezone ${nzOffset}).
TOMORROW is ${tomorrowLabel}.

Current stage: ${stage}
Turn count: ${turnCount}
Lead email: ${incoming.leadEmail}
Lead name (tentative): ${existing?.lead_name || incoming.leadName}${currentEventNote}

Available appointment slots (all times are NZ local time):
${slotsListForPrompt}

Conversation so far:
${historyText}

Respond with STRICT JSON only \u2014 no prose, no code fences.`;

return [{
  json: {
    ...incoming,
    isNewThread,
    stage,
    turnCount,
    history,
    slots,
    slotLabels,
    existingRow: existing,
    existingCalendarEventId: existing?.calendar_event_id || '',
    systemPrompt,
    userPrompt
  }
}];

// Parse Claude JSON response — hardened with fence stripping, schema validation, safe fallback
const llmItem = $input.first().json;
let llmRaw = llmItem.content?.[0]?.text || llmItem.text || llmItem.message?.content || llmItem.output || llmItem.response || JSON.stringify(llmItem);

// Strip markdown code fences (Claude sometimes wraps JSON)
llmRaw = llmRaw.replace(/```json?\n?/gi, '').replace(/```/g, '').trim();

let parsed = null;
try {
  const start = llmRaw.indexOf('{');
  const end = llmRaw.lastIndexOf('}');
  if (start !== -1 && end !== -1) {
    parsed = JSON.parse(llmRaw.substring(start, end + 1));
  }
} catch (e) {
  console.error('LLM JSON parse failed:', e.message);
}

// Validate required fields
if (parsed) {
  const requiredFields = ['next_stage', 'reply_body'];
  const missing = requiredFields.filter(f => !parsed[f]);
  if (missing.length > 0) {
    console.error('LLM response missing fields:', missing.join(', '));
    parsed = null; // fall through to fallback
  }
  // Validate next_stage is a known value
  const validStages = ['new', 'awaiting_details', 'awaiting_time_confirmation', 'appointment_confirmed', 'opted_out', 'stalled'];
  if (parsed && !validStages.includes(parsed.next_stage)) {
    console.error('LLM returned unknown stage:', parsed.next_stage);
    parsed.next_stage = 'stalled';
  }
}

// Safe fallback if parsing or validation failed
if (!parsed) {
  parsed = {
    next_stage: 'stalled',
    reply_body: 'Thanks for your message. One of the Lidgard Shades team will be in touch with you shortly.\n\nLidgard Shades team',
    confirmed_slot_iso: null,
    is_reschedule: false,
    extracted: {}
  };
}

const prep = $('Prepare LLM Input').first().json;
const inc = $('Extract & Guard').first().json;
const extracted = parsed.extracted || {};

const newHistory = [...(prep.history || [])];
newHistory.push({ role: 'assistant', content: parsed.reply_body, at: new Date().toISOString() });

const existing = prep.existingRow || {};
const existingCalendarEventId = existing.calendar_event_id || '';
const hasExistingEvent = !!existingCalendarEventId;

// Validate confirmed_slot_iso if present
let confirmedSlot = parsed.confirmed_slot_iso || null;
if (confirmedSlot) {
  const dt = new Date(confirmedSlot);
  if (isNaN(dt.getTime()) || dt < new Date()) {
    console.error('Invalid or past appointment time from LLM:', confirmedSlot);
    confirmedSlot = null;
    parsed.next_stage = 'awaiting_time_confirmation'; // re-ask
    parsed.reply_body += '\n\n(Could you confirm which time slot works for you?)';
  }
}

const tableRow = {
  threadId: prep.threadId,
  stage: parsed.next_stage || 'stalled',
  lead_name: extracted.lead_name || existing.lead_name || inc.leadName || '',
  lead_email: inc.leadEmail || existing.lead_email || '',
  blind_type: extracted.blind_type || existing.blind_type || '',
  property_address: extracted.property_address || existing.property_address || '',
  approx_size: extracted.approx_size || existing.approx_size || '',
  preferred_timeframe: extracted.preferred_timeframe || existing.preferred_timeframe || '',
  requested_time: extracted.requested_time || existing.requested_time || '',
  confirmed_time: confirmedSlot || existing.confirmed_time || '',
  calendar_event_id: existingCalendarEventId,
  phone_number: extracted.phone_number || existing.phone_number || '',
  turn_count: prep.turnCount,
  raw_history: JSON.stringify(newHistory),
  last_activity: new Date().toISOString()
};

const isAppointmentConfirmed = parsed.next_stage === 'appointment_confirmed' && !!confirmedSlot;
const isReschedule = !!parsed.is_reschedule || (isAppointmentConfirmed && hasExistingEvent);

return [{
  json: {
    ...inc,
    replyBody: parsed.reply_body,
    nextStage: parsed.next_stage,
    confirmedSlotIso: confirmedSlot,
    extracted,
    tableRow,
    leadName: tableRow.lead_name,
    blindType: tableRow.blind_type,
    propertyAddress: tableRow.property_address,
    approxSize: tableRow.approx_size,
    phoneNumber: tableRow.phone_number,
    isAppointmentConfirmed,
    existingCalendarEventId,
    hasExistingEvent,
    isReschedule
  }
}];

